<chapter>
  <title><xi:include href="../entities_en.xml" xpointer="ent_Swaption"
  xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" /> Module</title>

  <para role="TEXT">The <xi:include href="../entities_en.xml" xpointer="ent_Swaption"
  xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" /> module enables you, on behalf
  of your company, to arrange swaptions.</para>

  <para role="TEXT">For basic features common to all modules, such as basic terminology
  and the use of lists and forms, see chapter
  <emphasis>Introduction</emphasis>. For descriptions of functions, see
  chapter <emphasis>Functions</emphasis>.</para>

  <para role="TEXT">This chapter gives detailed descriptions of the input forms used by
  this module, and describes any features specific to this module.</para>

  <section role="ITEM">
    <title>Swaption Trades</title>

    <para role="TEXT">A swaption is an option to enter into a swap contract, either as an
    opening transaction or as an offsetting swap, that cancels an existing
    swap position. A payer's swaption is the right to be a fixed-rate payer
    and a receiver's swaption is the right to be a fixed-rate receiver. The
    settlement of a swaption is entry into the nominal exchange called for
    under the swap agreement. The strike is a specific (fixed) swap
    rate.</para>

    <para role="TEXT">Digital swaptions are also supported.</para>

    <para role="TEXT">Although Callable Swaps are entered as swaptions, the underlying
    swap is active and is handled by the system in the same way as any other
    swap. The Callable Swap window allows you to customize the generated
    callable/puttable and notice dates schedules.</para>

    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para role="TEXT">European Option</para>

        <para role="TEXT">A European-style swaption has a single expiry date on which it
        can be exercised. The preceding swaption example features a
        European-style swaption.</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para role="TEXT">Bermudan Option</para>

        <para role="TEXT">There are two categories of Bermudan Swaptions:</para>

        <itemizedlist>
          <listitem>
            <para role="TEXT">Fixed End Date</para>

            <para role="TEXT">The underlying of the option erodes as time passes. When the
            option is exercised, the underlying starts a few agreed upon days
            after the exercise (generally two business days).</para>
          </listitem>

          <listitem>
            <para role="TEXT">Fixed End Previous Start</para>

            <para role="TEXT">This category is a variant of the previous one. Only the
            start date of the underlying is different: all flows paid on or
            after the spot date that follows the exercise date are included in
            the underlying.</para>
          </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  </section>

